My example fits, if you weren't such a moron.  Bush started our involvement in the first Gulf War, just as Roosevelt started our involvement in WW II.  There is no difference.  Obviously Bush didn't make Saddam invade Iraq any more than Roosevelt forced Hitler or Hirohito to do what they did.  However, both leaders were responsible for leading the United States into armed conflict.  Then, as now, someone's political party or leaning has nothing to do with being pro or anti-war, this war or any other war.  Labeling someone a &quot;liberal&quot; or a &quot;conservative&quot; has no relevance in a discussion about whether they support a war or not, this war or any war.  <br>
