I did just that, and out of 750+ resolutions, no resolutions were made in 92-93, and I could only find 23 resolutions in 94 - 99, all but four about selling oil for humanitarian aid, and one about paying Iraqi nationals back for land lost to Kuwait.  None of them speaking of anything beyond &quot;severe consequences&quot; and most of them not even that (many deal with Iraq having issues with the oil economy and needing to sell more barrels than was allowed to make up shortfall in barrel price), and certainly nothing of &quot;all means necessary&quot;.  Compare that to the buildup to the first Gulf war, and the last 5 months, and yes, it became very much a back burner issue.  To attempt to say that for 12 years we have been waiting at this high level of expectation with the immediate threat of force in Saddam's face is a big stretch.<br>
